HEADWORD: Flacker
<hw>Flack"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>flakeren</ets>, fr. <ets>flacken</ets> to move quickly to and fro;
cf. icel. <ets>flakka</ets> to rove about, AS. <ets>flacor</ets>
fluttering, flying, G. <ets>flackern</ets> to flare, flicker.]</ety>
<def>To flutter, as a bird.</def> <mark>[Prov. Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Grose.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

